Marzel Everette RHODES, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 15694. United States Court of Appeals Ninth Circuit. Feb. 4, 1958. Marzel R. Rhodes, in pro. per. Charles P. Moriarty, U. S. Atty., Joseph C. McKinnon, Asst. U. S. Atty., Seattle, Wash., for appellee.

Before HEALY, FEE and BARNES, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The order below denying motion to set aside sentence pursuant to 28 U.S.C. § 2255 is affirmed.
